Character Creation
Following the Rulebook Character creation, with slight edits regarding the age of the Characters.

Attributes
Take one attribute at 4, three at 3, four at 2 and one at 1.

Skills
Pick one Skill distribution between Jack of all Trade, Balanced or Specialist:

Jack of all trades: One Skill at 3; eight Skills at 2; ten Skills at 1.

Balanced: Three Skills at 3; five Skills at 2; seven Skills at 1.

Specialist: One Skill at 4; three Skills at 3; three Skills at 2; three Skills at 1.

Add free specialties to Academics, Craft, Performance, and Science Skills. Take one more free specialty.

Disciplines
Choose 2 disciplines of your in-clan pool. Take 2 points in one, 1 point in another.

Caitiffs choose 2 discipline and do the same spread.

Thin-Blood characters have no intrinsic Discipline.

Humanity
Starting humanity is 7.

Reacquire lost dots at no exp cost up to your base humanity pool.

Increasing base pool costs 3x experience.

Experience
1 XP: Waking up and posting 3+ emotes/week.

1 XP: Interacting with another character.

1 XP: Progressing a story/reaching a desire.

1 XP: Participating in ST led scenes.

1 XP: Extremely evil (3+ stains) or 'heroic' acts.

Age and Ancillae Rules
Age Categories
Childer or Fledgling: Embraced within last 15 years. 12th/13th Gen. BP 1.

Neonates: Embraced 1940 to a decade ago. 12th/13th Gen. BP 1. Receive +15 experience points.

Ancillae: Embraced 1780 to 1940. Age not over 300 years. Max 10th Gen. BP 2. Receive +35 experience points and +2 extra advantage/flaw points.

Expanded Ancillae Rules (In Memoriam)
12th Generation: BP 1. 8 dots of Advantages, 12 XP for skills.

11th or 10th Generation: BP 2. 8 dots of Advantages, 3 dots of flaws.

9th or 8th Generation: BP 3. 5 dots of flaws.

Oceans of Time (Eras)
Up to 100 years ago: Choose 3 Eras. Receive Flaws of 1.

Up to 150 years ago: Choose 4 Eras. Receive Flaws of 2. Lose 1 permanent dot of Humanity.

Older than 150 years: Choose 5 Eras. Receive Flaws of 3. Lose 2 permanent dots of Humanity.

Merits, Flaws and Loresheets
Starting Points: 7 points to distribute between Merits, Backgrounds and Loresheets.

Loresheet Cap: Hard cap of 2 different loresheets at CC.

Bloodline Exception: A bloodline or a 'descendant of' loresheet are not included in this limit.

Soft Cap: Soft cap of 3 dots at CC. Do not approve more than one LS at that level.

Flaws: Every character has 2 points of flaws. Extra flaws give no extra merit points.
